The '''M4 carbine''' is a family of firearms tracing its lineage back to earlier [[carbine]] versions of the [[M16 rifle|M16]], all based on the original [[AR-15]] made by [[ArmaLite]]. It is a shorter and lighter version of the [[M16 rifle#M16A2|M16A2]] [[assault rifle]], with 80% parts commonality with the M16A2.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.specialoperations.com/Weapons/Features/M4/Page_Two.htm |title=The Design & Development of the M-4 Carbine |publisher=Special Operations.Com |accessdate=2008-11-08}}</ref> The '''M4''' has [[selective fire]] options including [[Semi-automatic firearm|semi-automatic]] and [[Burst mode (firearm)|three-round burst]] (like the M16A2), while the '''M4A1''' has a "[[Automatic firearm|full auto]]" option in place of the three-round burst.


